Full Description: MyBodyGallery.com allows people to see real bodies unmediated by the photographic manipulation and selection process that happens in advertising and popular culture. With a simple search tool, visitors can review user-submitted photos and data showing the variances in physiques among people of the same height, weight, and clothing size. Visitors can create user accounts to upload their own photos.  By helping people to objectively see what real bodies look like, MyBodyGallery.com promotes body positivity, nurtures acceptance of the fact that we are all beautiful, and offers community. Through browsing images of “real bodies” crowdsourced by everyday people, visitors to the website can help heal the damage caused to body image by media perpetuations of body shapes and sizes that are unrealistic for most people. As of February 2016, almost 62,000 users are currently registered to use the site. In the 6 years since MyBodyGallery.com launched, nearly 30,000 photos have been uploaded. Our site is viewed by an international community. We are most popular in the United States, Canada, the United Kingdom, Australia, and Finland. We know that to disrupt the way dog food is made and distributed we need the support of the local community. With your help we are disrupting the pet food industry.

Description: Google Patents is a search engine from Google that indexes patents and patent applications.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: Google Patents indexes more than 87 million patents and patent applications with full text from 17 patent offices, including: United States Patent and Trademark Office (USPTO), European Patent Office (EPO), China's National Intellectual Property Administration (CNIPA), Japan Patent Office (JPO), Korean Intellectual Property Office (KIPO), World Intellectual Property Organization (WIPO), Deutsches Patent- und Markenamt (DPMA), Canadian Intellectual Property Office (CIPO), Russia, UK, France, Spain, Belgium, Denmark, Finland, Luxembourg, the Netherlands. These documents include the entire collection of granted patents and published patent applications from each database (which belong to the public domain). US patent documents date back to 1790, EPO and WIPO to 1978.[2] Optical character recognition (OCR) has been performed on the older US patents to make them searchable, and Google Translate has been used on all non-English patents to make the English translations searchable. Google Patents also indexes documents from Google Scholar and Google Books, and has machine-classified them with Cooperative Patent Classification codes for searching. Patent litigation information is also available in Google Patents through a partnership with Darts-ip, a global patent litigation database.

Description: CMax Advisors is a consulting agency in Columbus, OH driven to help our clients build strong teams.
Full Description: CMax was started over 15 years ago with the goal of helping teams succeed. From the early days through today, CMax has had the privilege of working with some great companies. While the individual project or service varied, it was always around team development and growth. Whether it was building a talent pipeline, developing and delivering a leader program or helping a business owner complete a strategic plan, our goal was to build strong teams that would generate strong business performance. W﻿e delivered some great results, the opportunities to provide our services to additional companies increased. We experienced significant growth and expanded our service offerings and the markets we serviced. Growth was a key focus and we added several team members. This growth resulted in some unexpected challenges in our organization. The performance of our team declined and as a result, we had to persevere through some challenges. This experience gave us unique perspective into the impact that underperforming teams have on an organization’s performance. We learned that strong team performance begins with a strong foundation, leaders who are aligned to the strategy, and highly capable team members. As we enter the next phase of our journey, we are well positioned with proven methodologies and approaches to consult with our clients to improve their teams.
